Microsoft founder Bill Gates has ordered the world’s first hydrogen-powered superyacht worth an estimated $644 million (R9.6 billion). The Guardian reports that the Aqua ship – a 112-metre (370ft) luxury vessel completely powered by liquid hydrogen – includes a number of high-end features such as an infinity pool, helipad, spa and gym. According to the boat’s designers Sinot, the yacht has five decks and space to accommodate 14 guests and 31 crew members. <img class="size-full wp-image-372604 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Yacht-2.png" alt="" width="1451" height="770" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Yacht-2.png 1451w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Yacht-2-300x159.png 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Yacht-2-1024x543.png 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Yacht-2-768x408.png 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Yacht-2-1200x637.png 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px" /> <img class="size-full wp-image-372606 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Yacht-3.png" alt="" width="1313" height="883" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Yacht-3.png 1313w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Yacht-3-300x202.png 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Yacht-3-1024x689.png 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Yacht-3-768x516.png 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Yacht-3-1200x807.png 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px" /> <img class="size-full wp-image-372608 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Yacht-4.png" alt="" width="1329" height="892" srcset="htt